ERIC JACOBS, a former chairman of the SWD Cricket Scorers’ Association, was elected as the new chairman of the body on Saturday 4 June.Jacobs was elected to his position at the Scorers’ Association’s Annual General Meeting. The cricketing body is also associated to SWD Cricket.At the AGM Chadclan Solomons was elected as the new vice-chairman, Herculus Odendaal (training coordinator) was re-elected to the Executive Committee, and Emme-rentia Lamont will be the new secretary of the association.The position of treasurer is still vacant and will be filled at a Special General Meeting.